Boldface for tt:

## Debian/Ubuntu:
# Watch out!  If this wants to uninstall anything, you may be using texlive
# instead of tetex.  I don't know of a Debian/Ubuntu distribution for
# texlive (news: but as of 3/2009 there is one), so you'll have to follow
# the by-hand instructions below.
sudo apt install tetex-extra

## By hand
# Do this as root
cd /usr/share/texmf-texlive/fonts/source/public
wget http://www.ctan.org/get/fonts/cm/mf-extra/bold.zip
unzip bold.zip
mkdir /usr/share/texmf-texlive/tex/latex/bold-extra
cd /usr/share/texmf-texlive/tex/latex/bold-extra
wget ftp://cam.ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/misc/bold-extra.sty
texhash

===========================================================================

Something from CTAN:

# acronym, https://ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/acronym?lang=en
cd ~/tex/sty
BASENAME=acronym
wget https://mirrors.ctan.org/macros/latex/contrib/${BASENAME}.zip
unzip ${BASENAME}.zip
cd ${BASENAME}
latex ${BASENAME}.ins
(cd ..; ln -s ${BASENAME}/${BASENAME}.sty .)

# boxedminipage, https://ctan.org/pkg/boxedminipage
cd ~/tex/sty
BASENAME=boxedminipage
wget https://mirrors.ctan.org/macros/latex/contrib/${BASENAME}.zip
unzip ${BASENAME}.zip
cd ${BASENAME}
latex ${BASENAME}.ins
(cd ..; ln -s ${BASENAME}/${BASENAME}.sty .)

# textpos, http://www.astro.gla.ac.uk/users/norman/distrib/latex/#textpos
cd ~/tex/sty
wget http://www.astro.gla.ac.uk/users/norman/distrib/latex/textpos-1.4.tar.gz
tar xzf textpos-1.4.tar.gz
cd textpos-1.4
latex textpos.ins
(cd ..; ln -s textpos-1.4/textpos.sty .)
latex textpos.dtx
dvips -o textpos.ps textpos.dvi

